{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893483485,"sessionID":"ses_284804d43ffeBROLlqgk7jQYer","part":{"id":"prt_d7b800bc30017QSAeFmn21IYD5","messageID":"msg_d7b7ff8a9001GtV3q1ZaaPrgam","sessionID":"ses_284804d43ffeBROLlqgk7jQYer","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f59cb6fd3bc6404c8f037038c69e861c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775893483475,"end":1775893483483}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893483496,"sessionID":"ses_284804d43ffeBROLlqgk7jQYer","part":{"id":"prt_d7b800864001c9RjNWG55HsBFs","messageID":"msg_d7b7ff8a9001GtV3q1ZaaPrgam","sessionID":"ses_284804d43ffeBROLlqgk7jQYer","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-18c6ea6be14e4d61943d6e47af17c919","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-034 |\n8: | Module | .github |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: Establish a comprehensive CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions for the AgentCube project, automating build verification, code quality checks, testing, and release workflows. This proposal implements 12 workflows covering:\n17: \n18: 1. **Build Verification**: Docker image builds on pull requests\n19: 2. **Code Quality**: Go lint, Python lint (Ruff), spelling checks (codespell), copyright headers\n20: 3. **Testing**: Unit tests with coverage, E2E tests on Kind, Python SDK tests\n21: 4. **Code Generation**: Validation of generated artifacts\n22: 5. **Release**: Multi-architecture image publication to GitHub Container Registry\n23: 6. **Workflow Management**: Auto-approval for trusted contributors\n24: \n25: **Workflow Summary**:\n26: \n27: | Workflow | Purpose |\n28: |----------|---------|\n29: | `main.yml` | Docker build verification on PRs |\n30: | `e2e.yml` | End-to-end tests on Kind cluster |\n31: | `lint.yml` | Go linting (golangci-lint) |\n32: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK unit tests |\n33: | `python-lint.yml` | Python linting (Ruff) |\n34: | `test-coverage.yml` | Go test coverage reporting |\n35: | `codegen-check.yml` | Generated code validation |\n36: | `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright header consistency |\n37: | `codespell.yml` | Spelling verification |\n38: | `build-push-release.yml` | Image publication on main/tags |\n39: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify plugin packaging and publishing |\n40: | `workflows-approve.yml` | Auto-approve trusted contributor runs |\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n45: \n46: ### 2.1 In Scope\n47: \n48: | Deliverable | Description |\n49: |-------------|-------------|\n50: | `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Pull request Docker build verification |\n51: | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | Kind-based E2E testing workflow |\n52: | `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go linting with path filtering |\n53: | `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK pytest execution |\n54: | `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Ruff-based Python linting |\n55: | `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Go test coverage with Codecov integration |\n56: | `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Generated code drift detection |\n57: | `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright header validation |\n58: | `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Repository-wide spelling check |\n59: | `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Multi-arch image push to ghcr.io |\n60: | `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify plugin release automation |\n61: | `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | First-time contributor workflow approval |\n62: \n63: ### 2.2 Workflow Trigger Matrix\n64: \n65: | Workflow | Triggers | Branches | Path Filters |\n66: |----------|----------|----------|--------------|\n67: | `main.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | None |\n68: | `e2e.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | None |\n69: | `lint.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml` |\n70: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | — | `sdk-python/**` |\n71: | `python-lint.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py` |\n72: | `test-coverage.yml` | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | — | All minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` |\n73: | `codegen-check.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` |\n74: | `copyright-check.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | All minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` |\n75: | `codespell.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | None |\n76: | `build-push-release.yml` | `push` | `main`, tags `v*.*.*` | None |\n77: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | `push` tags | `dify-plugin/v*` | None |\n78: | `workflows-approve.yml` | `pull_request_target` | `main`, `release-**` | None |\n79: \n80: ### 2.3 Out of Scope\n81: \n82: | Item | Reason |\n83: |------|--------|\n84: | GitHub self-hosted runners | Using GitHub-hosted runners (ubuntu-latest) |\n85: | Custom CI infrastructure | Standard GitHub Actions suffices |\n86: | Third-party CI systems (Jenkins, GitLab CI) | GitHub-native solution preferred |\n87: | Deployment workflows | Deployment handled by Helm in clusters |\n88: | Security scanning (SAST/DAST) | Future AR for security tooling |\n89: | Performance benchmarks | Not in initial CI scope |\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n94: \n95: ### 3.1 新增文件\n96: \n97: | File | Description |\n98: |------|-------------|\n99: | `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Docker build workflow |\n100: | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | E2E test workflow |\n101: | `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go lint workflow |\n102: | `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK test workflow |\n103: | `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Python lint workflow |\n104: | `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Coverage workflow |\n105: | `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Codegen check workflow |\n106: | `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright check workflow |\n107: | `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Spelling check workflow |\n108: | `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Release build workflow |\n109: | `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify plugin publish workflow |\n110: | `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | Workflow approval workflow |\n111: \n112: ### 3.2 修改文件\n113: \n114: | File | Change |\n115: |------|--------|\n116: | None | All workflows are new additions |\n117: \n118: ### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n119: \n120: | Dependency | Purpose |\n121: |------------|---------|\n122: | `actions/checkout@v4` | Repository checkout |\n123: | `actions/setup-go@v5` | Go toolchain installation |\n124: | `actions/setup-python@v5` | Python toolchain installation |\n125: | `docker/setup-buildx-action@v3` | Docker Buildx setup |\n126: | `docker/login-action@v3` | Container registry authentication |\n127: | `docker/build-push-action@v5` | Multi-arch image builds |\n128: | `helm/kind-action@v1` | Kind cluster setup |\n129: | `dorny/paths-filter@v3` | Path-based workflow filtering |\n130: | `codecov/codecov-action@v4` | Coverage upload |\n131: | `github-script` | GitHub API operations |\n132: \n133: ### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n134: \n135: | Consumer | Usage |\n136: |----------|-------|\n137: | Pull Request authors | Automatic validation on PRs |\n138: | Maintainers | Quality gate enforcement |\n139: | Release process | Automated image publishing on tags |\n140: | Dify plugin users | Plugin availability via dify-plugins repo |\n141: | First-time contributors | Streamlined workflow approval |\n142: \n143: ### 3.5 Makefile Targets Required\n144: \n145: | Target | Workflow | Description |\n146: |--------|----------|-------------|\n147: | `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `e2e.yml` | Build workload manager image |\n148: | `docker-build-router` | `e2e.yml` | Build router image |\n149: | `docker-build-picod` | `e2e.yml` | Build picod image |\n150: | `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image |\n151: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n152: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n153: | `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run E2E test script |\n154: | `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | Cleanup E2E resources |\n155: | `lint` | `lint.yml` | Run golangci-lint |\n156: | `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code |\n157: | `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n162: \n163: ### Alternative 1: Single Monolithic Workflow\n164: \n165: **Approach**: Combine all CI steps into a single workflow file.\n166: \n167: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n168: |--------|------------|\n169: | Pros | Simpler structure, single file to maintain |\n170: | Cons | No parallel execution, longer feedback loop, all-or-nothing failure, no selective triggering |\n171: \n172: **Decision**: Rejected. Multiple workflows enable parallel execution, faster feedback, and path-based selective triggering. Critical checks (lint, build) complete faster than longer checks (E2E).\n173: \n174: ### Alternative 2: GitLab CI / Jenkins\n175: \n176: **Approach**: Use alternative CI/CD platforms.\n177: \n178: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n179: |--------|------------|\n180: | Pros | Potential for self-hosted infrastructure, different feature sets |\n181: | Cons | GitHub is the canonical repository; external CI adds complexity; no native GitHub integration |\n182: \n183: **Decision**: Rejected. GitHub Actions provides native integration with the repository, requires no external infrastructure, and uses the same platform as the code hosting.\n184: \n185: ### Alternative 3: Composite Actions for Reused Steps\n186: \n187: **Approach**: Extract common steps (setup, checkout) into composite actions.\n188: \n189: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n190: |--------|------------|\n191: | Pros | DRY principle, centralized maintenance |\n192: | Cons | Additional complexity for minimal code; current duplication is acceptable for clarity |\n193: \n194: **Decision**: Rejected for initial implementation. May reconsider if step duplication becomes unmanageable. Current workflow count (12) is manageable.\n195: \n196: ### Alternative 4: Dependabot for Action Versioning\n197: \n198: **Approach**: Use Dependabot to auto-update action versions.\n199: \n200: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n201: |--------|------------|\n202: | Pros | Automatic security updates, version tracking |\n203: | Cons | Adds dependency management overhead; pinning to major versions is sufficient |\n204: \n205: **Decision**: Rejected for now. Pinning to major versions (v3, v4, v5) provides stability while allowing minor updates. Can add Dependabot configuration in a future AR.\n206: \n207: ### Alternative 5: Reusable Workflows for Coverage\n208: \n209: **Approach**: Extract test-coverage.yml as a reusable workflow callable from other workflows.\n210: \n211: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n212: |--------|------------|\n213: | Pros | Reusability across multiple calling workflows |\n214: | Cons | Only test-coverage.yml uses `workflow_call`; no other callers exist |\n215: \n216: **Decision**: Partially adopted. `test-coverage.yml` already uses `workflow_call` for future reusability, but this is not the primary pattern for other workflows.\n217: \n218: ### Alternative 6: Self-Hosted Runners for E2E\n219: \n220: **Approach**: Use self-hosted runners with pre-configured Kind clusters for faster E2E.\n221: \n222: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n223: |--------|------------|\n224: | Pros | Faster E2E execution, persistent Kind clusters |\n225: | Cons | Infrastructure overhead, security considerations, maintenance burden |\n226: \n227: **Decision**: Rejected. GitHub-hosted runners provide consistent, isolated environments with zero maintenance overhead. E2E execution time is acceptable (~10-15 minutes).\n228: \n229: ### Alternative 7: Merge Queue with Branch Protection\n230: \n231: **Approach**: Use GitHub merge queues instead of PR-based checks.\n232: \n233: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n234: |--------|------------|\n235: | Pros | Ensures linear history, serialized merges |\n236: | Cons | Additional configuration, not needed for current team size |\n237: \n238: **Decision**: Rejected for now. `merge_group` trigger is supported in `test-coverage.yml` and `python-sdk-tests.yml` for future merge queue adoption. Current PR-based workflow is sufficient.\n239: \n240: ---\n241: \n242: ## 5. Risks\n243: \n244: | Risk | Mitigation |\n245: |------|------------|\n246: | Action version deprecation | Pin to major versions; monitor deprecation notices |\n247: | Rate limiting on GitHub Actions | Path filtering reduces unnecessary runs; workflow approval for first-time contributors |\n248: | E2E flakiness | Kind cluster isolation; artifact collection on failure; cleanup in `always()` block |\n249: | Registry credentials exposure | Use `GITHUB_TOKEN` (built-in) for ghcr.io; no long-lived secrets |\n250: | Coverage report size | Only cover `./pkg/...`; upload as artifact for large reports |\n251: | False positives in codespell | Temporary file removal for known false positives; ignore list for common issues |\n252: | Buildx cache growth | Use GitHub Actions cache; prune old caches periodically |\n253: \n254: ---\n255: \n256: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n257: \n258: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/` directory structure\n259: - [ ] Implement `main.yml` with Docker build verification\n260: - [ ] Implement `e2e.yml` with Kind cluster and test execution\n261: - [ ] Implement `lint.yml` with path filtering for Go files\n262: - [ ] Implement `python-sdk-tests.yml` with pytest execution\n263: - [ ] Implement `python-lint.yml` with Ruff configuration\n264: - [ ] Implement `test-coverage.yml` with Codecov integration\n265: - [ ] Implement `codegen-check.yml` with `make gen-check`\n266: - [ ] Implement `copyright-check.yml` with `make gen-copyright`\n267: - [ ] Implement `codespell.yml` with ignore list configuration\n268: - [ ] Implement `build-push-release.yml` with multi-arch builds\n269: - [ ] Implement `dify-plugin-publish.yml` with cross-repo PR creation\n270: - [ ] Implement `workflows-approve.yml` with contributor check\n271: - [ ] Add required secrets to repository settings (`CODECOV_TOKEN` optional, `PLUGIN_ACTION` for dify)\n272: - [ ] Configure branch protection rules requiring status checks\n273: - [ ] Test each workflow with sample PRs\n274: \n275: ---\n276: \n277: ## 7. References\n278: \n279: - GitHub Actions Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/actions\n280: - Docker Buildx Documentation: https://docs.docker.com/buildx/working-with-buildx/\n281: - Kind Documentation: https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/\n282: - golangci-lint: https://golangci-lint.run/\n283: - Ruff: https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/\n284: - Codecov: https://docs.codecov.com/\n285: - ci-cd/spec.md — CI/CD requirements specification\n286: - ci-cd/design.md — CI/CD design documentation\n287: - test/e2e/run_e2e.sh — E2E test execution script\n288: - Makefile — Build and test targets\n\n(End of file - total 288 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-034 |\n| Module | .github |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | L |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nEstablish a comprehensive CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions for the AgentCube project, automating build verification, code quality checks, testing, and release workflows. This proposal implements 12 workflows covering:\n\n1. **Build Verification**: Docker image builds on pull requests\n2. **Code Quality**: Go lint, Python lint (Ruff), spelling checks (codespell), copyright headers\n3. **Testing**: Unit tests with coverage, E2E tests on Kind, Python SDK tests","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775893483472,"end":1775893483494}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893483498,"sessionID":"ses_284804d43ffeBROLlqgk7jQYer","part":{"id":"prt_d7b800fb7001K09OzpHBlIVwXl","messageID":"msg_d7b7ff8a9001GtV3q1ZaaPrgam","sessionID":"ses_284804d43ffeBROLlqgk7jQYer","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f2bc8e5ee60642f4b12506f234947a0e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: import os\n2: import datetime\n3: import logging\n4: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n5: \n6: from agentcube.clients.control_plane import ControlPlaneClient\n7: from agentcube.clients.code_interpreter_data_plane import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n8: from agentcube.utils.log import get_logger\n9: \n10: \n11: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n12:     \"\"\"Main client for Code Interpreter sessions with lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n13: \n14:     def __init__(\n15:         self,\n16:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n17:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n18:         ttl: int = 3600,\n19:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n20:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n21:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n22:         verbose: bool = False,\n23:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n24:     ) -> None:\n25:         self.name = name\n26:         self.namespace = namespace\n27:         self.ttl = ttl\n28:         self.verbose = verbose\n29:         self._logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n30: \n31:         self.router_url = self._resolve_router_url(router_url)\n32: \n33:         self._cp_client = ControlPlaneClient(\n34:             workload_manager_url=workload_manager_url,\n35:             auth_token=auth_token,\n36:         )\n37:         self._session_id: Optional[str] = None\n38:         self._session_created: bool = False\n39:         self._dp_client: Optional[CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient] = None\n40: \n41:         if session_id:\n42:             self._session_id = session_id\n43:             self._session_created = False\n44:             self._init_data_plane()\n45:         else:\n46:             self._session_id = self._cp_client.create_session(\n47:                 name=self.name,\n48:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n49:                 ttl=self.ttl,\n50:             )\n51:             self._session_created = True\n52:             self._init_data_plane()\n53: \n54:     def _resolve_router_url(self, router_url: Optional[str]) -> str:\n55:         \"\"\"Resolve router URL from argument or environment.\"\"\"\n56:         if router_url:\n57:             return router_url\n58:         url = os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n59:         if url:\n60:             return url\n61:         raise ValueError(\"router_url must be provided via argument or ROUTER_URL environment variable\")\n62: \n63:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None:\n64:         \"\"\"Initialize the data plane client.\"\"\"\n65:         if self._session_id is None:\n66:             raise RuntimeError(\"session_id must be set before initializing data plane\")\n67:         try:\n68:             self._dp_client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n69:                 session_id=self._session_id,\n70:                 router_url=self.router_url,\n71:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n72:                 cr_name=self.name,\n73:             )\n74:         except Exception as e:\n75:             if self._session_created and self._session_id:\n76:                 self._logger.warning(f\"Data plane init failed, cleaning up session: {e}\")\n77:                 self._cp_client.delete_session(self._session_id)\n78:                 self._session_id = None\n79:             raise\n80: \n81:     def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\":\n82:         \"\"\"Enter context manager.\"\"\"\n83:         return self\n84: \n85:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n86:         \"\"\"Exit context manager, calling stop().\"\"\"\n87:         self.stop()\n88: \n89:     def execute_command(\n90:         self,\n91:         command: str,\n92:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n93:     ) -> str:\n94:         \"\"\"Execute a command in the code interpreter.\n95: \n96:         Args:\n97:             command: Command to execute.\n98:             timeout: Timeout in seconds.\n99: \n100:         Returns:\n101:             stdout from command execution.\n102:         \"\"\"\n103:         if self._dp_client is None:\n104:             raise RuntimeError(\"Data plane client not initialized\")\n105:         return self._dp_client.execute_command(command, timeout)\n106: \n107:     def run_code(\n108:         self,\n109:         language: str,\n110:         code: str,\n111:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n112:     ) -> str:\n113:         \"\"\"Run code in the code interpreter.\n114: \n115:         Args:\n116:             language: Programming language (python, py, python3).\n117:             code: Code content to run.\n118:             timeout: Timeout in seconds.\n119: \n120:         Returns:\n121:             stdout from code execution.\n122:         \"\"\"\n123:         if language not in (\"python\", \"py\", \"python3\"):\n124:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {language}. Supported: python, py, python3\")\n125: \n126:         timestamp = datetime.datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d_%H%M%S\")\n127:         filename = f\"/workspace/code_{timestamp}.py\"\n128: \n129:         self.write_file(code, filename)\n130:         return self.execute_command(f\"python3 {filename}\", timeout)\n131: \n132:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n133:         \"\"\"Write content to a file in the code interpreter.\n134: \n135:         Args:\n136:             content: File content.\n137:             remote_path: Path to write to.\n138:         \"\"\"\n139:         if self._dp_client is None:\n140:             raise RuntimeError(\"Data plane client not initialized\")\n141:         self._dp_client.write_file(content, remote_path)\n142: \n143:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n144:         \"\"\"Upload a local file to the code interpreter.\n145: \n146:         Args:\n147:             local_path: Local file path.\n148:             remote_path: Remote destination path.\n149:         \"\"\"\n150:         if self._dp_client is None:\n151:             raise RuntimeError(\"Data plane client not initialized\")\n152:         self._dp_client.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)\n153: \n154:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n155:         \"\"\"Download a file from the code interpreter.\n156: \n157:         Args:\n158:             remote_path: Remote file path.\n159:             local_path: Local destination path.\n160:         \"\"\"\n161:         if self._dp_client is None:\n162:             raise RuntimeError(\"Data plane client not initialized\")\n163:         self._dp_client.download_file(remote_path, local_path)\n164: \n165:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n166:         \"\"\"List files in the code interpreter workspace.\n167: \n168:         Args:\n169:             path: Directory path to list.\n170: \n171:         Returns:\n172:             List of file information.\n173:         \"\"\"\n174:         if self._dp_client is None:\n175:             raise RuntimeError(\"Data plane client not initialized\")\n176:         return self._dp_client.list_files(path)\n177: \n178:     def stop(self) -> None:\n179:         \"\"\"Stop the client, closing connections and deleting session if created.\"\"\"\n180:         if self._dp_client:\n181:             self._dp_client.close()\n182:             self._dp_client = None\n183: \n184:         if self._session_created and self._session_id:\n185:             self._cp_client.delete_session(self._session_id)\n186: \n187:         self._cp_client.close()\n188:         self._session_id = None\n\n(End of file - total 188 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"import os\nimport datetime\nimport logging\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nfrom agentcube.clients.control_plane import ControlPlaneClient\nfrom agentcube.clients.code_interpreter_data_plane import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\nfrom agentcube.utils.log import get_logger\n\n\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    \"\"\"Main client for Code Interpreter sessions with lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py","time":{"start":1775893483477,"end":1775893483497}}}}
